<p><img src="https://cdn3.brettterpstra.com/uploads/2025/03/keyboard-header-pink-rb.7486.jpg" width="800" height="226" style="margin:0 auto;clear:both;" class="header" /></p>

<p>I recently <a href="https://brettterpstra.com/2025/03/24/keybindings-home-row-arrow-cluster/">published a Karabiner trick</a> that turned
<span class="keycombo separated" title="Semicolon"><kbd class="key symbol">;</kbd></span> plus <span class="keycombo separated" title="J"><kbd class="key symbol">J</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="I"><kbd class="key symbol">I</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="K"><kbd class="key symbol">K</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="L"><kbd class="key symbol">L</kbd></span> into arrow keys. I&rsquo;ve
determined that my implementation could use some work.
Here&rsquo;s the redux.</p>

