<p>Now you can hold down <span class="keycombo separated" title="Semicolon"><kbd class="key symbol">;</kbd></span> and use
<span class="keycombo separated" title="J"><kbd class="key symbol">J</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="I"><kbd class="key symbol">I</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="K"><kbd class="key symbol">K</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="L"><kbd class="key symbol">L</kbd></span> as arrow keys, and key repeat,
switching between directions, and modifier-based selections
will all work smoothly. Hold down <span class="keycombo separated" title="Single Quote"><kbd class="key symbol">'</kbd></span> and use the
same keys to navigate with <span class="keycombo separated" title="Home Key"><kbd class="key symbol">&#8598;</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="Page Up Key"><kbd class="key symbol">&#8670;</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="Page Down Key"><kbd class="key symbol">&#8671;</kbd></span><span class="keycombo separator">/</span><span class="keycombo separated" title="End Key"><kbd class="key symbol">&#8600;</kbd></span>.
Enjoy!</p>

